Short:    the best (AGA only) pong clone (with curve balls etc..)
Author:   S.A.Z. Huybrechts (Bash)
Uploader: bash@stack.urc.tue.nl
Type:     game/misc

Solid 2 is the improved AGA version of Solid (released in 1993). The game is totally reprogrammed.
All bugs are removed. All graphics are now full AGA. Modules are replaced. More soundeffects are
now included. All resulted in a more playable (with new features like the possibility to give balls
curving effects).


System Requirements:
--------------------
* Any AMIGA with AGA chipset. The code is totally 68000 based, so future (?) AGA Amiga's based on a
68000 will also satisfy. The game is tested on both A1200 and A4000/30.

* Over 1 Mb of chipram (all recent AGA Amiga's). 'Cause the game is crunched (with the StoneCracker
cruncher) fast ram is desirable. If the game won't load (and no error messages occur), make a
bootable disk (with startup-sequence, without workbench loading procedure) and try to start the game
from that disk.


Game Options:
-------------
You can play Solid with one player, or against each other. All possible input combinations of mouse
and joystick are provided. If you want to play the game against the computer, you will always be
player 1. Keys used in the options-menu:

        F1 - Player 1 uses joystick port 1      F6 - Player 2 uses joystick port 2
        F2 - Player 1 uses joystick port 2      F7 - Player 2 uses mouse port 2
        F3 - Player 1 uses mouse port 1         F8 - Player 2 is the computer (CPU)

        ESC - Leave Solid

Press a fire button to start the game.


The Game:
---------
The objective of the game is to win 3 sets of 15 points before your opponent does. The score of both
players is at the top of the screen. Watch out: The computer improves during playing. Try to beat it,
it will not be as easy as it looks the first set !
Keys used during the game:

        P   - Pause on/off
        ESC - Leave the game and return to the options-menu

Press the fire button to give the ball curve effect in the direction your bat is moving. If someone
wins the game (no ESC is pressed) there will appear a winner screen. Pressing a fire button will
result in leaving this screen and return to the options-menu.


