Technical Information:
----------------------
The game is totally written in assembly using the Trash'm-One assembler (by Deftronic of Crionics).
The lenght of the sourcecode is 95607 bytes (consisting of 4616 lines). All this is combined with
graphics made in DPaint IV, converted in Image Fx and finally converted by my own iffconverter. Some
graphics are raytraced in Real 3D. Sounds are sampled with the Megalosound and Audiomaster sampler
programs. The modules are taken from the src.doc.ic.ac.uk FTP site. Finally the total game is
crunched with the StoneCracker cruncher. All this was done on my A4000/30 and the A1200's of the
other members of the Vanquish crew.

